The Internet of Things (IoT) significantly influences daily life, with trends indicating substantial adoption and integration across various sectors such as healthcare, transportation, and home automation. As of 2020, approximately 26.66 billion IoT devices were active globally, with projections estimating that this number will exceed 75 billion by 2025. Recent statistics demonstrate considerable IoT adoption, including major advancements in healthcare, transportation, and home automation, ultimately reshaping everyday life.